data.title: What is Methanol, its uses, energies
data.meta_description: Methanol is a wood alcohol (CH3OH) that can be used as a renewable energy, marine and auto fuel, and as fuel cells. Because methanol is a versitile chemical, it can be feedstock for many applications.
data.text:
About the Methanol Institute

The Methanol Institute (MI) serves as the trade association for the global methanol industry, representing the world’s leading producers, distributors, shippers, and technology companies. MI now represents its members from five offices around the world in Singapore, Washington DC, Beijing, Brussels, and Delhi.

About Methanol

Methanol — the simplest alcohol (CH3OH) — is a chemical building block for hundreds of everyday products, including plastics, paints, car parts and construction materials. Methanol also is a clean energy resource used to fuel cars, trucks, buses, ships, fuel cells, boilers and cook stoves.
